               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18160110-83-person774">
                  THOMAS 
                  HAYLETT
               <interp inst="t18160110-83-person774" type="surname" value="HAYLETT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160110-83-person774" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160110-83-person774" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18160110-83-viclabel474" type="occupation">shoe-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18160110-83-victim773 t18160110-83-viclabel474"></join>, on <placeName id="t18160110-83-crimeloc475">Holborn Hill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18160110-83-crimeloc475" type="placeName" value="Holborn Hill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18160110-83-crimeloc475" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18160110-83-off472 t18160110-83-crimeloc475"></join>. I lost my shoes on the 23rd of December; they were inside the shop, in a glazed window. I left my little boy to watch the shop, while I went into the yard, and in the meantime, this person came in, and took the shoes. When I returned, I found the child crying; he told me the man was gone up the Hill; I followed him about three hundred yards, and took him with the shoes under his coat.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18160110-83-person775">
                  THOMAS 
                  HAYLETT
               <interp inst="t18160110-83-person775" type="surname" value="HAYLETT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160110-83-person775" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18160110-83-person775" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , JUNIOR. I am six years old. My father left me to mind the shop while he went to the yard. I went into the parlour to play at marbles, and that man there (pointing to the prisoner,) came into the shop, and stole away the shoes.</p>

